WEBVTT

00:03.770 --> 00:06.039
I hope I'm not late
for Barbara's karate competition.

00:06.106 --> 00:07.240
[CHUCKLES]

00:07.307 --> 00:10.710
You know, what's it like having
a girlfriend who can kick your butt?

00:10.777 --> 00:13.346
She cannot kick my butt!

00:13.413 --> 00:17.650
Please. She can kick it, flip it
and throw it across the room.

00:17.717 --> 00:19.052
You're right.

00:19.119 --> 00:21.488
-I got to learn karate.
-I could teach you.

00:23.890 --> 00:25.458
[BOTH LAUGH]

00:25.525 --> 00:26.526
What?

00:26.593 --> 00:29.362
You take karate
with your little friends in kindergarten?

00:29.429 --> 00:31.831
No. My dad works on a cruise ship.

00:31.898 --> 00:33.500
And while we were docked in Japan,

00:33.566 --> 00:36.803
I studied martial arts
at the Tokugawa Academy.

00:36.870 --> 00:37.871
[SCOFFS]

00:37.937 --> 00:41.107
Yeah, and I learned to fly while
my rocket ship was docked on Mars.

00:41.174 --> 00:42.275
[LAUGHS]

00:42.342 --> 00:43.476
No, really.

00:48.882 --> 00:50.650
Ooh! That was cute, kid.

00:50.717 --> 00:53.386
-[CHUCKLES]
-[DINGS]

00:53.453 --> 00:54.721
-Whoa.
-Wow!

00:54.788 --> 00:56.489
Can you teach me how to-- Ooh!

00:59.259 --> 01:02.195
I could have thrown you further,
but I didn't warm up.

01:06.332 --> 01:08.501
<i>♪ Here I am in your life ♪</i>

01:08.568 --> 01:13.573
<i>♪ Here you are in mine</i>
<i>Yes, we have a suite life ♪</i>

01:13.640 --> 01:15.709
<i>♪ Most of the time ♪</i>

01:15.775 --> 01:17.510
<i>♪ You and me</i>
<i>We got the world to see ♪</i>

01:17.577 --> 01:19.979
<i>♪ So come on down ♪</i>

01:20.046 --> 01:24.651
<i>♪ Just me and you know what to do</i>
<i>So come on down ♪</i>

01:24.718 --> 01:25.719
<i>♪ It's you and me ♪</i>

01:25.785 --> 01:29.756
<i>♪ And me and you</i>
<i>We got the whole place to ourselves ♪</i>

01:29.823 --> 01:34.494
<i>♪ You and me, we got it all for free</i>
<i>So come on down ♪</i>

01:34.561 --> 01:36.963
<i>♪ This is the suite life ♪</i>

01:39.399 --> 01:42.469
<i>♪ We've got a suite life ♪</i>

01:47.073 --> 01:49.342
-[DIALING]
-Did someone lose their cell phone?

01:49.409 --> 01:50.877
How do you know it's not mine?

01:50.944 --> 01:52.078
[SCOFFS]
Please.

01:52.145 --> 01:54.614
That phone costs
more than your entire wardrobe.

01:54.681 --> 01:57.617
Then again, so does this candy bar.

01:57.684 --> 02:04.057
London, for the last time, a Thousand-
Dollar bar does not cost $1000.

02:05.458 --> 02:08.495
Then Nia owes me a lot of change.

02:08.561 --> 02:09.796
I'll go put this in the lost and found.

02:09.863 --> 02:10.997
Oh! Wait. I have an idea!

02:11.064 --> 02:13.433
You better say it quickly
before it dies of loneliness.

02:14.167 --> 02:17.070
Let's check out the phone
and see what stuff is on it.

02:17.137 --> 02:18.972
[PLAYS VIVALDI'S "SPRING"]

02:19.039 --> 02:21.374
That's Vivaldi. I love Vivaldi!

02:21.441 --> 02:23.143
No, his name is David. See?

02:23.209 --> 02:24.477
[GASPS]

02:24.544 --> 02:26.880
Ooh, his wallpaper is Van Gogh's Irises.

02:26.946 --> 02:28.415
That's my favorite painting!

02:28.481 --> 02:29.616
We have so much in common!

02:29.683 --> 02:32.018
Gee, you found your perfect match.

02:32.085 --> 02:33.920
I now pronounce you phone and wife.

02:36.156 --> 02:40.527
[PLAYING VIVALDI'S "SPRING"]

02:41.861 --> 02:43.496
Isn't botany fascinating?

02:43.563 --> 02:46.132
Oh, yeah. I love flowers.

02:46.199 --> 02:48.401
How'd you like to study these two lips?

02:53.573 --> 02:54.841
Well, that's a start.

02:55.875 --> 02:59.279
Zack, we're here to study,
and you've got a lot to learn.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.048
Hey, I'm willing to stay after school.

03:03.016 --> 03:04.284
Good-bye.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.286
[SIGHS]

03:06.353 --> 03:09.055
Well, looks like it's just you and me.

03:11.925 --> 03:13.927
BOTH:
<i>Konichiwa,</i> Zack-san!

03:15.462 --> 03:18.465
Right back at you, San and San.

03:19.833 --> 03:25.538
Travis is teaching me how to be a master
at karate so I can impress Barbara.

03:26.239 --> 03:30.710
[WAILING]

03:33.446 --> 03:36.750
Man, I wish I could find
a way to impress Dakota.

03:36.816 --> 03:38.718
Yeah? Just don't show her
your report card.

03:38.785 --> 03:42.756
[LAUGHS]

03:42.822 --> 03:43.823
That's not funny.

03:45.592 --> 03:49.162
You know, I won Barbara over
by cooking her a gourmet meal.

03:49.229 --> 03:53.233
Oh. Great idea, except I can't cook.

03:53.299 --> 03:54.934
I can help you out.

03:55.001 --> 03:58.405
I learned how to be a gourmet chef
when dad's ship was docked in Monte Carlo.

03:58.471 --> 04:01.608
-Did you know that Monaco is also a ta--
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

04:01.675 --> 04:03.143
So, you going to help me out this weekend?

04:03.209 --> 04:05.445
-Sure.
-Hey, hey, hey.

04:05.512 --> 04:07.881
-He's helping me.
-I can help you both.

04:07.947 --> 04:09.916
And maybe after that,
we can all go bowling.

04:09.983 --> 04:11.518
I've never been bowling before.

04:11.584 --> 04:15.622
So you've run with the bulls in Pamplona,
but you've never been bowling?

04:15.689 --> 04:18.158
Yeah. Dad thinks it's dangerous.

04:18.224 --> 04:19.225
Go figure.

04:20.460 --> 04:22.195
Well, you got yourself a deal.

04:24.898 --> 04:27.233
-Whoa!
-Hyah!

04:27.300 --> 04:28.702
Why did you do that?

04:28.768 --> 04:32.706
Lesson number one, expect the unexpected.

04:33.840 --> 04:36.810
Yeah. You know,
I'd write that down, but my hand is numb.

04:37.777 --> 04:40.447
[CHUCKLES]

04:40.513 --> 04:41.514
That's not funny.

04:43.817 --> 04:44.818
Pardon me, miss.

04:44.884 --> 04:46.820
Uh, I lost a phone here yesterday.

04:46.886 --> 04:48.588
And I found one.

04:48.655 --> 04:50.290
It must be Kismet.

04:50.357 --> 04:51.358
No, it's David.

04:51.424 --> 04:54.494
[GIGGLES]
Hi, David.

04:54.561 --> 04:55.895
[BELL DINGS]

04:57.697 --> 04:58.698
Well, thank you.

04:58.765 --> 04:59.899
[LAUGHS]

04:59.966 --> 05:04.471
You know, I'm a cellist on my way
to perform Vivaldi's <i>Four Seasons.</i>

05:04.537 --> 05:05.805
Would you be my guest?

05:05.872 --> 05:08.208
[SIGHS]
I'd love to.

05:08.274 --> 05:10.877
But I don't have a formal gown handy.

05:13.113 --> 05:16.883
[SIGHS]
It's beautiful!

05:16.950 --> 05:18.785
Where did you get it?

05:20.186 --> 05:22.222
Where did you get it?

05:23.456 --> 05:26.026
Where did you get it?

05:26.092 --> 05:28.261
From the dirty clothes pile.

05:30.230 --> 05:31.965
We ran out of quarters.

05:32.032 --> 05:33.099
Sorry.

05:33.166 --> 05:36.536
I was just dreaming
about this guy whose phone I found.

05:36.603 --> 05:40.073
He's a rich, charming cellist
who works to save the rainforest.

05:40.140 --> 05:41.474
[SQUEALS]

05:42.409 --> 05:43.610
You can tell all that from a phone?

05:43.677 --> 05:45.512
And more.

05:45.578 --> 05:48.848
This Thursday, he's volunteering
at the Feed the Needy Foundation.

05:48.915 --> 05:50.984
That's my favorite charity!

05:51.051 --> 05:52.619
They catered my aunt's wedding.

05:53.920 --> 05:55.855
Where was she registered, a pawn shop?

05:56.923 --> 05:57.924
Maybe.

06:10.236 --> 06:11.805
Ooh. Wow. Impressive!

06:11.871 --> 06:13.406
You can beat up a pillow.

06:14.808 --> 06:17.210
You know,
that Travis kid has taught me a lot.

06:17.277 --> 06:18.845
You've only had two lessons.

06:18.912 --> 06:20.013
What could he have taught you?

06:20.080 --> 06:21.715
The Sleep of the Striking Cobra.

06:21.781 --> 06:23.216
There's no such thing as the Sleep--
[SNORES]

06:26.019 --> 06:28.188
Wow! It worked!

06:28.254 --> 06:29.356
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:29.422 --> 06:30.757
Come in.

06:31.558 --> 06:32.592
Hey, Barbara.

06:32.659 --> 06:34.828
Hey, Cody.

06:34.894 --> 06:37.897
-Why are you wearing a gi?
-Well, I'm learning karate, too.

06:37.964 --> 06:39.366
I've been practicing on Zack.

06:39.432 --> 06:42.402
Ahh. Sleep of the Striking Cobra.

06:42.469 --> 06:44.671
Yeah. And I've learned
much more than that.

06:44.738 --> 06:45.739
Check this out.

06:47.073 --> 06:51.544
Ow, ow, ow! Ow, ow, ow! Ow, ow, ow!
Ow, ow, ow! Ow, ow, ow!

06:51.611 --> 06:52.812
[GROANS]

06:52.879 --> 06:56.082
Well, maybe you can still
beat me up, but not for long.

06:56.149 --> 06:58.284
Why does it matter if I can beat you up?

06:58.351 --> 07:02.856
Because I'm the guy and you're the girl,
and the guys are supposed to be tougher.

07:02.922 --> 07:04.591
And by the way,
you're bruising my sternum.

07:06.559 --> 07:08.595
What a sexist attitude.

07:08.661 --> 07:10.897
I thought you were more evolved than that.

07:10.964 --> 07:13.333
I am. It's just...

07:13.400 --> 07:15.869
I don't people to think
that I'm the weaker sex.

07:15.935 --> 07:18.505
Oh, so, now I have
to be weak to be with you?

07:18.571 --> 07:21.307
No. Not weak. Just weaker.

07:22.542 --> 07:24.878
Oh, well, if that's the way you feel,
then forget it.

07:24.944 --> 07:27.013
No, no, no! That's not what I meant!

07:27.080 --> 07:28.815
-You see--
-Oh, I don't want to hear it.

07:28.882 --> 07:29.883
[SNORES]

07:37.824 --> 07:38.825
Here you go.

07:38.892 --> 07:39.926
I charged the battery.

07:39.993 --> 07:41.661
Thanks for saving my phone.

07:41.728 --> 07:43.930
Now, I'm off to save the rainforest.

07:45.532 --> 07:46.800
All by yourself?

07:46.866 --> 07:50.770
Actually, I was hoping
to take along a spunky blond.

07:50.837 --> 07:52.472
I'm spunky and blond!

07:53.807 --> 07:55.141
I dye my roots brown.

08:05.852 --> 08:06.886
Madeline?

08:08.688 --> 08:11.524
Why are you hanging on my tie?

08:11.591 --> 08:13.560
Oh! Sorry, sir.

08:13.626 --> 08:15.195
I thought it was a vine.

08:15.261 --> 08:18.198
She's having another fantasy
about the guy who owns that phone.

08:18.264 --> 08:19.766
-[GIGGLES]
-Madeline,

08:19.833 --> 08:21.701
if you found a phone,
you must put it in lost and found.

08:21.768 --> 08:23.003
No!

08:23.069 --> 08:26.940
It would break my heart if the phone rang
and someone else answered it.

08:27.007 --> 08:28.842
[PLAYS VIVALDI'S "SPRING"]

08:28.908 --> 08:30.210
-I'll get it!
-What?

08:30.276 --> 08:32.545
Hello! Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

08:32.612 --> 08:34.247
Okey-doke. Bye, David.

08:35.315 --> 08:36.316
That was David.

08:37.751 --> 08:39.219
Really?

08:39.285 --> 08:40.687
What did he say?

08:40.754 --> 08:42.422
He's coming to pick this phone up at 5.

08:42.489 --> 08:44.357
[GASPS]
He's coming here?

08:44.424 --> 08:46.259
I have to get my hair done!

08:46.326 --> 08:47.794
I have to buy a ball gown!

08:47.861 --> 08:49.996
I have to find a pith helmet!

08:52.866 --> 08:54.834
Whoo. Can you spell, desperate?

08:54.901 --> 08:56.436
How many chances do I get?

09:06.346 --> 09:08.114
Maddie? What are you still doing here?

09:08.181 --> 09:09.849
David didn't show up.

09:09.916 --> 09:11.751
Oh, I'm sorry.

09:11.818 --> 09:13.620
How could he have not shown up?

09:13.687 --> 09:16.289
I mean, this is the night we're supposed
to finally meet and fall in love

09:16.356 --> 09:17.757
and swing off on a vine.

09:19.225 --> 09:22.462
Honey, I love
that you are a true romantic, but...

09:22.529 --> 09:26.499
did it ever occur to you that maybe,
to him, this is just picking up a phone?

09:26.566 --> 09:29.069
Oh, no. No, no.
We're meant to be together.

09:29.135 --> 09:33.340
I mean, we both love Vivaldi
and Van Gogh and the rainforest and--

09:33.406 --> 09:36.209
[GASPS]
We're not meant to be together!

09:36.276 --> 09:38.678
No! That's not necessarily true.

09:38.745 --> 09:40.880
-All I meant was that--
-I know what you meant.

09:40.947 --> 09:43.416
When am I going to learn
that life is not a fairy tale?

09:43.483 --> 09:45.251
-That there are no storybook endings?
-But--

09:45.318 --> 09:49.656
I'm going to wind up bitter
and all alone, just like you!

09:49.723 --> 09:51.424
[WEEPS]

09:54.728 --> 09:56.062
Glad I could help.

10:02.402 --> 10:05.338
-And then, on the 17th day of our trip,
-Uh-huh.

10:05.405 --> 10:09.109
me and Dad crossed the international
date line, and he was on one side,

10:09.175 --> 10:10.744
-and I was on the other.
-Uh-huh.

10:10.810 --> 10:13.013
And when he told me
to do something right now, I told him,

10:13.079 --> 10:15.448
"I already did that yesterday!"

10:15.515 --> 10:18.918
-[LAUGHS]
-Oh, that's fascinating.

10:18.985 --> 10:22.589
-Phew.
-Hey, can I borrow Travis for a second?

10:22.655 --> 10:26.426
Oh, second, minute, century,
yesterday, tomorrow, I really don't care.

10:27.761 --> 10:28.895
Oh.

10:28.962 --> 10:31.164
Hey, Cody, we still on for bowling later?

10:31.231 --> 10:34.367
Yeah, yeah, sure.
But first, I need a favor.

10:34.434 --> 10:37.003
Do you know anything
about Japanese tea ceremonies?

10:37.070 --> 10:38.304
What don't I know?

10:39.406 --> 10:41.741
First documented
in the Edo period, tea cer--

10:41.808 --> 10:43.343
Yeah, yeah, yeah. I get it. Look.

10:44.177 --> 10:46.546
I found out my girlfriend
and her grandmother

10:46.613 --> 10:48.048
are coming here tomorrow for tea,

10:48.114 --> 10:50.717
and I want to perform
a Japanese tea ceremony for them.

10:50.784 --> 10:53.987
To master the tea ceremony
takes a lifetime.

10:54.054 --> 10:55.221
I got a day.

10:56.389 --> 10:57.390
Good luck.

10:58.892 --> 11:01.594
-But Travis--
-Okay, okay.

11:01.661 --> 11:03.797
I'll write down
everything you need to know,

11:03.863 --> 11:07.600
because there are many gestures
that must be performed in a certain order.

11:11.104 --> 11:12.939
Is that the first gesture in the ceremony?

11:13.006 --> 11:14.641
No, my shorts are just riding up.

11:19.179 --> 11:21.915
Hurry up! Dakota's
going to be here any minute.

11:21.981 --> 11:24.384
Sorry. I got a late start.
I had to help your brother.

11:24.451 --> 11:26.586
Ahh, forget him. He's a loser.

11:26.653 --> 11:28.888
Funny. He said the same thing about you.

11:30.190 --> 11:31.758
So, Zack,
we're still going bowling, right?

11:31.825 --> 11:32.892
Sure, sure.

11:32.959 --> 11:35.195
But it's important
that Dakota thinks I cooked this food.

11:35.261 --> 11:37.063
So stay back here and be quiet.

11:39.899 --> 11:41.568
Oh, a rice paper screen.

11:41.634 --> 11:44.004
Not unlike the ones
they use in Southern Thailand

11:44.070 --> 11:46.072
-for the ancient art of shadow puppetry--
-Yeah, yeah, whatever.

11:46.139 --> 11:47.841
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

11:47.907 --> 11:49.242
Zack, door!

11:50.477 --> 11:51.644
Ahh. My bad.

11:56.883 --> 11:57.884
Hey, Zack.

11:57.951 --> 11:59.719
-Ready to study?
-Oh, yes.

11:59.786 --> 12:03.056
Sure. But not on an empty stomach.

12:05.058 --> 12:06.393
Here you go. Try one of these.

12:08.261 --> 12:11.097
[CRUNCHES]
Mmm.

12:11.164 --> 12:12.499
You know, this is delicious.

12:12.565 --> 12:14.200
TRAVIS: Thanks.
-A lot.

12:14.267 --> 12:15.669
Thanks, thanks a lot.

12:17.937 --> 12:22.342
You know, it's eating something
I learned in gourmet chef school.

12:22.409 --> 12:26.279
-It is called--
TRAVIS: Foie Gras en Coupe.

12:26.346 --> 12:27.814
Frog paw with fruit.

12:29.215 --> 12:31.418
You mean Foie Gras en Coupe.

12:31.484 --> 12:33.520
Well, we can talk, or we can eat.

12:35.121 --> 12:36.289
Wow, Zack.

12:36.356 --> 12:38.158
You're a lot more sophisticated
than I thought.

12:38.224 --> 12:40.694
[CHUCKLES]
An understandable mistake.

12:40.760 --> 12:44.631
You were misled by my boyish charm
and my priceless collection of...

12:45.732 --> 12:47.133
action figures.

12:49.836 --> 12:50.837
Hi, Maddie.

12:50.904 --> 12:52.205
How did things go with your phone guy?

12:52.272 --> 12:53.406
He never showed up.

12:53.473 --> 12:54.841
Oh, honey.

12:54.908 --> 12:57.243
So, this time,
you were dumped before you met the guy?

12:58.645 --> 13:01.014
Oh, well. It saved you a lot of time.

13:01.081 --> 13:04.184
You know, I don't care
if I ever hear from David again.

13:04.250 --> 13:06.319
-[CELL PHONE PLAYS VIVALDI'S "SPRING"]
-It's David.

13:08.355 --> 13:10.790
Ooh, it's a text message.

13:10.857 --> 13:12.926
"Sorry I didn't show.

13:12.992 --> 13:14.627
Got held up at medical school."

13:14.694 --> 13:15.995
[GASPS]

13:16.062 --> 13:17.897
He's studying to be a doctor.

13:18.732 --> 13:20.934
Probably for the poor!

13:23.436 --> 13:25.372
-Scalpel.
-Scalpel!

13:26.473 --> 13:28.208
-Sponge.
-Sponge!

13:28.908 --> 13:30.977
-Lips.
-Lips.

13:32.912 --> 13:34.547
Uh, excuse me.

13:36.182 --> 13:37.350
Excuse me.

13:40.086 --> 13:41.388
Excuse me.

13:41.454 --> 13:42.555
Excuse me.

13:43.456 --> 13:45.025
Why are you kissing that sofa cushion?

13:47.093 --> 13:48.461
Because...

13:48.528 --> 13:51.698
we had a pillow fight,
and now, we're making up.

13:51.765 --> 13:53.099
Got to go.

13:53.166 --> 13:55.802
Konichiwa--
[STAMMERS]

13:57.537 --> 13:58.738
Oh.

14:01.675 --> 14:03.610
I hope Travis numbered these.

14:05.512 --> 14:08.848
But why did he have to do it in Japanese?

14:14.421 --> 14:16.122
All right, next, try this dish.

14:19.225 --> 14:20.960
Mmm. Fondue.

14:21.027 --> 14:22.662
I'm fond of you, too.

14:29.703 --> 14:30.970
Uh...

14:31.037 --> 14:33.206
Excuse me for a second.

14:34.474 --> 14:36.376
Okay. I just need you for a sec, okay?

14:36.443 --> 14:37.544
What are you doing here?

14:37.610 --> 14:39.179
I got to borrow Travis now.

14:39.245 --> 14:41.047
Uh-uh. Forget it.

14:41.114 --> 14:43.116
Look, I'll have him back in 10 minutes.

14:43.183 --> 14:45.618
Well, how are you going to get him out
of here without Dakota seeing him?

14:54.260 --> 14:55.595
Sorry to disturb you.

14:55.662 --> 14:58.331
Just had to borrow a cup of sugar.

14:58.398 --> 14:59.399
Oh!

15:03.169 --> 15:05.705
I should really see a doctor about this.

15:05.772 --> 15:07.674
Yeah, you should.

15:07.741 --> 15:08.808
Good-bye.

15:14.280 --> 15:17.017
Let me guess. You didn't cook the meal.

15:17.083 --> 15:19.452
[SIGHS]
All right.

15:19.519 --> 15:20.954
I can't lie to you.

15:21.588 --> 15:26.659
The truth is, is I dropped out of gourmet
chef school to join the Marines.

15:26.726 --> 15:27.761
Hoo-hah!

15:28.695 --> 15:29.696
[SIGHS]

15:31.398 --> 15:33.500
More like, ha-ha.

15:33.566 --> 15:34.868
Come on, Zack.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.736
All right.

15:36.803 --> 15:38.438
I had a little help.

15:38.505 --> 15:41.307
But I only wanted to impress you.

15:41.374 --> 15:45.578
Well, maybe it's the frog paw talking,
but you did.

15:45.645 --> 15:47.147
Really?

15:47.213 --> 15:50.684
Any guy who goes to this much trouble
deserves a second chance.

15:54.954 --> 15:58.224
Hey. Even when I'm bad, I'm good.

15:58.291 --> 15:59.359
[LAUGHS]

16:00.093 --> 16:01.628
You know, you guys really
don't have to be here.

16:01.695 --> 16:03.997
Oh, we want to see
the man behind the phone.

16:04.064 --> 16:06.399
See, Maddie? There are happy endings.

16:06.466 --> 16:07.500
It may not be so happy.

16:07.567 --> 16:09.903
For all we know, he could be hideous.

16:09.969 --> 16:11.905
I don't care what he looks like.

16:11.971 --> 16:14.040
He could be short, tall, fat, or thin.

16:14.107 --> 16:17.377
Excuse me. Um, I'm looking for Maddie?

16:17.444 --> 16:18.712
You left out old.

16:20.780 --> 16:22.482
-I'm Maddie.
-Ahh.

16:22.549 --> 16:24.084
-You must be David.
-Yeah.

16:24.150 --> 16:26.119
I could tell by your phone,
you have a lot of class.

16:26.186 --> 16:27.587
-Mmm.
-Class of '22.

16:27.654 --> 16:28.922
-[LAUGHS]
-Okay. That's-- you know what?

16:28.988 --> 16:30.256
-Enough of that.
-I'm sorry.

16:30.323 --> 16:32.225
[INDISTINCT]

16:32.292 --> 16:33.293
Here's your phone.

16:33.360 --> 16:36.096
I'd like to thank you
for taking care of my phone for me.

16:36.162 --> 16:37.964
May I buy you a hot chocolate?

16:39.132 --> 16:41.468
-I'd love that.
-Good.

16:41.534 --> 16:42.802
[MADDIE GIGGLES]

16:42.869 --> 16:45.005
By the time they get there,
it ain't going to be hot.

16:46.206 --> 16:47.207
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

16:57.117 --> 16:58.118
Oh.

17:00.186 --> 17:03.356
-Konichiwa.
-Cody, what are you doing here?

17:03.423 --> 17:08.294
Uh, I wanted to honor your grandmother by
performing the traditional tea ceremony.

17:08.361 --> 17:11.965
-[SPEAKS JAPANESE]
<i>-Arigato.</i>

17:12.032 --> 17:13.466
Give me a break-o.

17:14.768 --> 17:19.973
As you know, the water jar represents...

17:23.143 --> 17:24.744
the sun.

17:24.811 --> 17:28.648
And the bowl represents...

17:28.715 --> 17:29.716
uh...

17:33.053 --> 17:34.154
the butt?

17:35.255 --> 17:37.357
Oh! The moon! The moon!

17:37.424 --> 17:38.958
Oy vey.

17:39.893 --> 17:42.862
You should do so well at this.

17:42.929 --> 17:44.297
I know how to do it.

17:44.364 --> 17:46.366
And besides, it's usually done by a woman.

17:46.433 --> 17:49.402
I'm trying to prove
to you that I'm not a sexist pig.

17:49.469 --> 17:52.172
Oh! I believe you're not a pig boy.

17:52.238 --> 17:55.742
-Please, continue.
-<i>Arigato.</i>

18:03.350 --> 18:06.219
Oh! Very good.

18:06.286 --> 18:09.989
Do you see how he's meditating
over the fukusa?

18:10.056 --> 18:12.025
[INSECT BUZZING]

18:14.994 --> 18:18.431
[INSECT BUZZING]

18:22.369 --> 18:25.538
[INSECT BUZZING]

18:25.605 --> 18:28.108
Now he's really freaking me out.

18:30.577 --> 18:33.079
-[GRUNTS]
-[ALL SCREAM]

18:33.146 --> 18:34.781
Oh, I'm sorry.

18:34.848 --> 18:38.952
-[ALL SCREAM]
-[PANTING]

18:39.019 --> 18:42.589
Man, that bee was bigger than a blimp.

18:42.655 --> 18:43.857
Thanks a lot.

18:43.923 --> 18:46.693
Well, excuse me
for being allergic to bees.

18:46.760 --> 18:48.661
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

18:48.728 --> 18:50.063
Excuse me.

18:50.130 --> 18:51.264
Pardon me.

18:51.331 --> 18:52.799
That was great, Cody.

18:52.866 --> 18:55.435
I've never seen a traditional
Japanese bee ceremony before.

18:55.502 --> 18:58.638
-[LAUGHS]
-You mean you're not mad?

19:00.106 --> 19:04.377
How could I be mad when you went
to so much effort to impress my Obasan?

19:04.444 --> 19:06.012
I really did it for you, Barbara.

19:06.079 --> 19:07.580
Oh, Cody.

19:07.647 --> 19:09.115
Oh, Barbara!

19:11.785 --> 19:13.420
Oh, gross!

19:18.191 --> 19:19.659
Come on, Cody!

19:19.726 --> 19:22.529
Barbara and Dakota are waiting
for us to take them ice skating.

19:22.595 --> 19:23.663
[SCOFFS]

19:23.730 --> 19:24.964
Nice makeup, mom.

19:26.399 --> 19:29.035
This is an Amazon mud mask.

19:29.102 --> 19:33.473
According to Travis, it's been keeping
tribal women wrinkle-free for centuries.

19:33.540 --> 19:34.941
And single.

19:36.176 --> 19:37.610
[DOORBELL RINGS]

19:40.914 --> 19:42.849
Hiya, guys. You ready to bowl?

19:42.916 --> 19:44.551
-Hi, Ms. Martin.
-Hi, sweetie.

19:46.052 --> 19:48.221
Gee, Travis.

19:48.288 --> 19:51.758
You know, I feel really bad,
but the thing is...

19:51.825 --> 19:53.093
We got dates, dude.

19:53.159 --> 19:54.461
Catch you tomorrow.

19:54.527 --> 19:59.632
I wish, but my ship leaves tonight and
we won't be back for, like, seven years.

19:59.699 --> 20:03.937
Ooh. Well, in that case, see you then!

20:05.472 --> 20:06.473
Okay.

20:07.440 --> 20:09.442
Looking good in that mask, Ms. Martin.

20:09.509 --> 20:10.510
See you.

20:11.745 --> 20:12.746
[SQUEAKS]

20:15.181 --> 20:17.484
After everything Travis did for you two,

20:17.550 --> 20:19.719
you should be ashamed of yourselves.

20:19.786 --> 20:23.289
If I could move my face underneath
this mask, I would be so frowning at you.

20:31.464 --> 20:33.733
Travis, we're so glad you're still here.

20:33.800 --> 20:36.202
Look. We changed our minds.
We want to go bowling with you.

20:36.269 --> 20:39.039
It was my idea. Cody was against it,
but, you know, I talked him into it.

20:40.340 --> 20:42.008
Gee, guys. Sorry.

20:42.075 --> 20:43.910
But I made other plans.

20:43.977 --> 20:45.679
Ok. We're ready.

20:45.745 --> 20:47.981
But those are our girls.

20:48.048 --> 20:53.286
Well, as the Tibetan Sherpas say,
"when you meet on a narrow mountain path,

20:53.353 --> 20:56.189
-move over.
-[GIRLS LAUGH]

20:57.257 --> 21:00.093
-But Dakota--
-Don't "but Dakota" me.

21:00.160 --> 21:03.163
How could you stand up this sweet,
adorable little kid?

21:03.229 --> 21:05.865
Yeah. Look at that--
[INDISTINCT]

21:07.167 --> 21:08.368
Come on, Travi.

21:11.338 --> 21:14.040
You cannot just take our girlfriends.

21:14.107 --> 21:18.845
Guys, I'm about to go to sea
for seven years.

21:18.912 --> 21:20.080
Let me have this.

21:22.215 --> 21:23.717
BOTH:
Anchors aweigh.

21:31.491 --> 21:33.126
I can't believe
how much we have in common.

21:33.193 --> 21:34.194
I know.

21:34.260 --> 21:37.497
You like 300-year-old music,
I'm 300 years old.

21:38.798 --> 21:40.200
I like Van Gogh.

21:40.266 --> 21:41.267
I knew Van Gogh.

21:41.334 --> 21:43.703
[LAUGHS]
You are so funny.

21:43.770 --> 21:44.771
So are you.

21:44.838 --> 21:47.707
I hope you don't mind my asking,
but are you single?

21:47.774 --> 21:49.676
Oh, David.
[GIGGLES]

21:49.743 --> 21:51.811
I am so flattered, but...

21:51.878 --> 21:54.381
my mom doesn't let me
go out with anyone older than me.

21:54.447 --> 21:56.850
Neither does my mom.

21:56.916 --> 21:58.985
I was asking for my grandson.

21:59.052 --> 22:01.821
He's exactly like me,
except his hips are original.

22:02.922 --> 22:05.058
Are you ready, Grandpa? We're going
to be late for the Vivaldi--

22:05.725 --> 22:08.395
-Hello.
-David?

22:08.461 --> 22:11.231
-No, it's Jeffery.
-Oh, right.

22:11.297 --> 22:12.465
Sorry.

22:12.532 --> 22:15.201
It's just-- Somehow,
it seems like we met before.

22:15.268 --> 22:18.204
-He just broke up with his girlfriend.
-Oh, what a shame. My name is Maddie.

22:20.807 --> 22:21.875
Do you believe in fairy tales?

22:21.941 --> 22:23.777
Not so fast.

22:23.843 --> 22:25.545
This ramp is uphill.
